</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Basically there isn't much difference between MJ and alcohol, both in excess are really bad for the human body.  The reason why one is legal and the other isn't is due mainly to the fact of who profits and uses these substances.
<br />
MJ for example was made illegal first in the border areas of the United States because the primary consumers were Indio/Mexican.
<br />
Opium became illegal because it was the drug of choice for Chinese Immigrants (at the time were widely discriminated against) and it was spreading in the white female population.
<br />
The original reasons why many drugs were made illegal had nothing to do with the medicinal consequences of taking them.
<br />

<br />
My personal opinion is that if something like alcohol/nicotine can be legal, might as well make Marijuana legal.  Of course the arguement could then be made to legalize all drugs.<span class="gensmall"></span>


