				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The only reason drugs are illegal and alcohol isn't, is that drinking was around way before our country, but the drugs came into the society later.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The use of traditional 'drugs' (I say this because alcohol is one, hell even caffiene to an extent) has been around since the beginning of early civilization.
<br />
Coca, peyote and marijuana have been around/ingested/smoked as long as fermented oats and barley have.  They aren't by any means new to mankind or even American/European society.
<br />
The only difference being who consumed, sold and benefitted from the substances being available in the United States.  If it was based on some type of logic or sound reasoning, alcohol and probably nicotine as well, would be outlawed.<span class="gensmall"></span>


