			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">I'm obviously conservative, and a loyal Republican. This is one of the few issues I disagree with the party. I do not want all drugs legalized, if it is HIGHLY addictive, and incredibly unhealthy to you or others, then I would support criminalization. Criminalizing marijuana fails both tests.
<br />

<br />
Marijuana is at worst, mildly addictive, and a fairly easy habit to break if you absolutely have to with no physical withdrawel. Medical consequences of marijuana are extremely insignificant, and does not impair your ability to operate a vehicle to nearly the same degree as legal drugs.
<br />

<br />
The arguement that Marijuana should be legal because it is equally dangerous as alchohol is fundamentally flawed. In reality, alchohol and tobacco are both far, far worse.
<br />

<br />
I would support status quo for Cocaine, Heroin, etc (and dont give me any crap about Marijuana being a gateway drug, the only thing it leads you to, is snacking.). However, criminalization of Marijuana without similar sanctions of the far more harmful Tobacco and Alchohol, in light of Marijuana's relatively benign nature, is ludicrous.<span class="gensmall"></span>


				</div></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
