				<td colspan="2"><div class="postbody">Well actually, marijuana has been known to cause serious health problems for some.  However, the same can be said for cigarettes, alcohol, and Big Macs.  There is always going to be that small percentage of folks who have body chemistries that don't exactly jive with everything they come into contact with in life.  For the most part, MJ is a relatively benign substance, health-wise.  It should be made legal, they should tax the hell out of it, and release non-violent cannabis users from prison.  Hell, they can even impose the same restrictions that alcohol currently has (minimum age required to buy, no smoking and driving, etc).  The downfall of Western Civilization will not come about as a result.
<br />

